comments.body:
BuildHTTPClientWithHeaders stores the caller-provided map in the transport. Because maps are mutable and not thread-safe, a caller mutating the map after creating the client could cause a data race during RoundTrip. Consider copying extraHeaders into a new map (or converting to http.Header) inside BuildHTTPClientWithHeaders so the transport has an immutable snapshot.
```suggestion
	headers := make(map[string]string, len(extraHeaders))
	for k, v := range extraHeaders {
		headers[k] = v
	}

	base := &httputil.Transport{Transport: http.DefaultTransport}
	return &http.Client{
		Transport: &headerInjectingTransport{wrapped: base, headers: headers},
```

```suggestion
	SiteURL *string `json:"siteURL,omitempty" mapstructure:"siteURL"`

	// SiteTitle is forwarded as X-Title for OpenRouter attribution.
	// Optional but recommended so OpenRouter can identify your application.
	SiteTitle *string `json:"siteTitle,omitempty" mapstructure:"siteTitle"`
```

